[81.0, 855.5, 700.7, 866.3]}, {"text": "major allele (reference group).", "bbox": [81.0, 868.2, 194.6, 877.0]}, {"text": "łReduced numbers in multiple regression models are due to limited maternal genotype data and removal of outliers, consequently, these reduced numbers may in part", "bbox": [81.0, 876.9, 700.7, 887.7]}, {"text": "account for the lack of significance seen with some predictor variables. Note also that mean methylation levels were utilized for multiple regression modelling despite", "bbox": [81.0, 889.6, 700.7, 898.4]}, {"text": "not always demonstrating the strongest effect size with individual predictors. Standardised beta coefficients are obtained by first standardizing all variables to have a", "bbox": [81.0, 900.3, 700.8, 909.1]}, {"text": "mean of 0 and a standard deviation of 1, they denote the increase in methylation for a standard deviation increase in the predictor variables. Multiple regression analysis", "bbox": [81.0, 911.0, 700.7, 919.8]}, {"text": "was not performed for ZNT5 associations as mean methylation was not considered across this locus.", "bbox": [81.0, 921.7, 461.3, 930.5]}, {"text": "doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0033290.t003", "bbox": [81.0, 932.4, 225.1, 941.2]}, {"text": "PLoS ONE | www.plosone.org 5 March 2012 | Volume 7 | Issue 3 | e33290", "bbox": [103.7, 953.5, 700.8, 963.6]}]}